@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Premium civic AI platform for citizens and operations teams";
}

<div class="container py-4 civic-page">
    <section class="hero-panel mb-4">
        <div class="row align-items-center g-5">
            <div class="col-lg-7 position-relative">
                <span class="eyebrow">Civic resilience command platform</span>
                <h1 class="display-4 mt-3 mb-3">CivicOps AI turns scattered civic reports into structured municipal action.</h1>
                <p class="lead">Citizen reporting, department routing, area alerts, AI-assisted triage, and transparent status tracking for real communities.</p>
                <p class="text-muted-strong">Gemini runs only after explicit actions and falls back deterministically when unavailable. Humans stay in control, WhatsApp remains optional connector-ready support, and CivicOps never replaces emergency services.</p>
                <div class="command-strip mt-4">
                    <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/app"><i class="bi bi-phone me-2"></i>Open Citizen App</a>
                    <a class="btn btn-outline-info btn-lg" href="/Home/Dashboard">Municipal Dashboard</a>
                    <a class="btn btn-outline-light btn-lg" href="/Home/Agent">AI Agent</a>
                    <a class="btn btn-outline-warning btn-lg" href="/Home/BobEvidence">Bob Evidence</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5 position-relative">
                <div class="control-map">
                    <span class="eyebrow">Live demo operating picture</span>
                    <h2 class="h3 mt-2">Area signals → department action</h2>
                    <p>Chatsworth, Phoenix, Umlazi, Durban CBD, Pinetown, KwaMashu, Clermont, Isipingo and Amanzimtoti are represented in synthetic civic workloads.</p>
                    <div class="map-node" style="left:18%; top:30%"></div><div class="map-node" style="left:42%; top:22%"></div><div class="map-node" style="left:67%; top:38%"></div><div class="map-node" style="left:56%; top:68%"></div><div class="map-node" style="left:26%; top:72%"></div>
                    <div class="position-absolute bottom-0 start-0 end-0 p-3">
                        <div class="ops-card mb-0">
                            <div class="row g-3 text-center">
                                <div class="col-4"><div class="metric">100+</div><small class="text-muted-strong">seed reports</small></div>
                                <div class="col-4"><div class="metric">13</div><small class="text-muted-strong">departments</small></div>
                                <div class="col-4"><div class="metric">2</div><small class="text-muted-strong">product faces</small></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="row g-4 mb-4">
        <div class="col-lg-6"><div class="ops-card h-100">
            <span class="eyebrow">Public / citizen product</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">A real citizen companion.</h2>
            <p>The Citizen App and web portal support resident login, issue submission, reference tracking, area alerts, followed suburbs/wards, Copilot actions and lightweight local incident discussion threads.</p>
            <div class="d-flex flex-wrap mb-3"><span class="area-chip">Report issue</span><span class="area-chip">Photo placeholder</span><span class="area-chip">Voice-note ready</span><span class="area-chip">Track reference</span><span class="area-chip">Community thread</span></div>
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/citizen-app">Open Download / Install Hub</a>
        </div></div>
        <div class="col-lg-6"><div class="ops-card h-100">
            <span class="eyebrow">Staff / ops control room</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">Department queues with auditability.</h2>
            <p>Dispatchers and department responders see scoped queues, priority signals, routing reasons, AI-generated citizen responses, department briefs, alert recommendations and status history.</p>
            <div class="d-flex flex-wrap mb-3"><span class="area-chip">Water</span><span class="area-chip">Electricity</span><span class="area-chip">Roads</span><span class="area-chip">Waste</span><span class="area-chip">Disaster</span><span class="area-chip">Safety</span></div>
            <a class="btn btn-outline-info" href="/Auth/Login">Open Staff Login</a>
        </div></div>
    </section>

    <section class="ops-card mb-4">
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-4"><span class="eyebrow">How it works</span><h2 class="h1">From report to route in four controlled steps.</h2></div>
            <div class="col-lg-8"><div class="grid-auto">
                <div class="ops-stat"><strong>01 Intake</strong><p>Residents report via Citizen App/PWA or web with location, text, media placeholder and emergency disclaimer.</p></div>
                <div class="ops-stat"><strong>02 AI enrichment</strong><p>Gemini routine/premium models are configured server-side for explicit actions only; fallback is deterministic and professional when Gemini is unavailable.</p></div>
                <div class="ops-stat"><strong>03 Human review</strong><p>Staff review queue, routing reason, public response, alert recommendation and full audit notes.</p></div>
                <div class="ops-stat"><strong>04 Public status</strong><p>Residents track a reference, follow area alerts and add local context in simple incident/area threads.</p></div>
            </div></div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="grid-auto mb-4">
        <div class="ops-card"><i class="bi bi-cpu fs-1 text-info"></i><h3 class="h5 mt-3">Gemini + fallback, honestly surfaced</h3><p>Every AI action displays whether Gemini or local deterministic routing produced the result, including last model/action diagnostics.</p><a href="/Home/Agent" class="btn btn-outline-info">Open AI Assistant</a></div>
        <div class="ops-card"><i class="bi bi-bell fs-1 text-info"></i><h3 class="h5 mt-3">Area awareness</h3><p>Alerts cover planned maintenance, outages, weather disruptions, roads, waste and public safety across realistic demo areas.</p><a href="/Home/Alerts" class="btn btn-outline-info">View Area Alerts</a></div>
        <div class="ops-card"><i class="bi bi-kanban fs-1 text-info"></i><h3 class="h5 mt-3">Operations dashboard</h3><p>Information-dense control-room dashboard with department workload, high priority queues and scoped access paths.</p><a href="/Home/Dashboard" class="btn btn-outline-info">Enter Control Room</a></div>
        <div class="ops-card"><span class="badge bg-secondary">Optional connector</span><i class="bi bi-whatsapp fs-2 text-success d-block mt-3"></i><h3 class="h6 mt-3">WhatsApp stays secondary</h3><p>Connector-ready for future pilots or sandbox testing. The primary channels are the Citizen App, web portal and staff control room.</p><a href="/Home/Connectors" class="btn btn-outline-light btn-sm">Connector matrix</a></div>
    </div>

    <section class="hero-panel">
        <div class="row align-items-center g-4">
            <div class="col-lg-8"><span class="eyebrow">Judge-ready path</span><h2 class="section-title">Show the two faces in under five minutes.</h2><p class="lead">Start with the Citizen App, submit a messy report like “Pheonix streetlight out near school”, track the public reference, then switch to staff control room to show normalized area, routing, audit trail and department scope.</p></div>
            <div class="col-lg-4 d-grid gap-2"><a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/Home/DemoTour">Launch Demo Tour</a><a class="btn btn-outline-info btn-lg" href="/Home/BobEvidence">Bob Evidence</a></div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
